From: Hermes Workflow <kernel@local>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 11:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] kmi: declare+export android_vh_throttle_direct_reclaim_bypass

OPLUS's out-of-tree module oplus_bsp_zram_opt.ko (part of the
hybridswap/zram stack on OnePlus Nord CE5, OOS16) registers the
vendor hook android_vh_throttle_direct_reclaim_bypass via
register_trace_android_vh_throttle_direct_reclaim_bypass().

This hook exists in OPLUS's kernel tree but is NOT present in the
WildKernels GKI 6.1 source. As a result the symbol
__tracepoint_android_vh_throttle_direct_reclaim_bypass is undefined,
the module fails to load with "Unknown symbol", and the whole
zram/hybridswap module chain never initializes -> /dev/block/zram0
and /sys/block/zram0/hybridswap_meminfo never appear.

Ignoring vermagic/CRC (modversion patch) does NOT fix this: a missing
symbol is a hard load failure, unrelated to version magic.

Declaring the hook in trace/hooks/mm.h and exporting it from
drivers/android/vendor_hooks.c provides the three required symbols
(__tracepoint_/__traceiter_/__SCK__tp_func_) so the module resolves
and loads.

The signature TP_PROTO(bool *bypass) was reverse-engineered from the
module callback vh_android_vh_throttle_direct_reclaim_bypass(): it
takes the tracepoint data pointer plus one argument (a bool* that the
callback writes to). This matches the convention of the existing
*_bypass hooks in this header.

---
--- a/include/trace/hooks/mm.h
+++ b/include/trace/hooks/mm.h
@@ -318,6 +318,9 @@ DECLARE_HOOK(android_vh_filemap_map_pages_range,
 DECLARE_HOOK(android_vh_calculate_totalreserve_pages,
 	TP_PROTO(bool *skip),
 	TP_ARGS(skip));
+DECLARE_HOOK(android_vh_throttle_direct_reclaim_bypass,
+	TP_PROTO(bool *bypass),
+	TP_ARGS(bypass));
 #endif /* _TRACE_HOOK_MM_H */
 
 /* This part must be outside protection */
--- a/drivers/android/vendor_hooks.c
+++ b/drivers/android/vendor_hooks.c
@@ -343,3 +343,4 @@ EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_read_pages);
 EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_alloc_pages_reclaim_bypass);
 EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_alloc_pages_failure_bypass);
+EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_throttle_direct_reclaim_bypass);
 EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_madvise_pageout_swap_entry);
